[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Badlands (Alberta) banner.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Alberta Badlands"]}," is a region in the south-east of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Alberta"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Canada"]]},".  Flat wheat fields and ranchlands are common things that come to mind to describe it, but it is also an area rich with aboriginal history, interesting badland and hoodoo formations and a paleontology hotbed.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Cities"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Brooks"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Cambria (Alberta)"],["Cambria"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Drumheller"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["East Coulee"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Medicine Hat"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Other destinations"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\n\nThis region is where you find the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Alberta badlands"]},", a kind of weird and wonderful eroded landscape. ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Badlands"]]}," are also found to the south in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["North Dakota"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["South Dakota"]]}," in the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["United States"]]},".  The best single destination for viewing the Alberta badlands is ",{"type":"'''","value":["Dinosaur Provincial Park"]}," near ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Brooks"]]},".\n\nThere are a number of good ",{"type":"'''","value":["fossil"]}," beds and exhibits in this region. Top among them are the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Royal Tyrrell Museum"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Drumheller"]]},", and ",{"type":"'''","value":["Dinosaur Provincial Park"]}," near ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Brooks"]]},".  They are 177 km apart, and each demands a day or two of attention, so allow at least three days to see them all. Both feature interpretive tours, that are also easy to moderate hikes, during the summer months.\n\n",{